<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="78" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,348,438,464]" box="[227,348,438,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,438,464]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,438,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1436,485,582]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[353,541,485,511]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[353,541,485,511]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Stroborineceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[549,655,486,512]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with weakly depressed, rounded-pentagonal whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.20), venter concave, ventrolateral shoulder angular. Whorls not embracing. Ornament with five faint spiral ridges located on the flank.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="78" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,362,621,647]" box="[227,362,621,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,362,621,647]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,362,621,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,1436,667,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
From the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[421,470,667,693]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felis">
<emphasis box="[421,470,667,693]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">felis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘cat’ and referring to the characteristic whorl profile resembling a cat’s head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
