<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="79" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[227,372,985,1011]" box="[227,372,985,1011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,985,1011]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,985,1011]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[226,1439,1032,1270]" lastBlockId="12.[226,1436,507,568]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="79" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,1032,1058]" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Holotype</typeStatus>
<collectionCode box="[342,389,1032,1059]" country="Portugal" name="Universidade de Lisboa, Museu Bocage" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">MB</collectionCode>
.C.30454 is a phragmocone fragment of slightly less than 90 degrees in length (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1394,1032,1058]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[229,272,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-276@11.[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Stroborineceras felis gen. et sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30454 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Whorl profile. C. Suture line, at ww =15.6 mm, wh=12.7 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902603/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). It reaches a whorl height of 
<quantity box="[527,610,1068,1094]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="78" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
and the profile is weakly depressed (ww/wh = 1.22). The characteristic whorl profile has the outline of a cat’s head shape (
<figureCitation box="[840,931,1103,1129]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[229,272,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-276@11.[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Stroborineceras felis gen. et sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30454 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Whorl profile. C. Suture line, at ww =15.6 mm, wh=12.7 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902603/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="78">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); its general shape is rounded-pentagonal. The venter is concavely incurved and is bordered by the very prominent, angular ventrolateral shoulder. The profile is widest at the middle of the whorl height; from here the flanks converge with a slight concave incurvation. The dorsum is broadly rounded. On the flank about five spiral lines are visible; they become weaker towards the dorsum. The suture line shows a deep, almost semicircular external lobe, a subacute ventrolateral saddle, a shallow, very broadly rounded lateral lobe and a very broad, low internal saddle (
<figureCitation box="[414,504,542,568]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[229,272,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-276@11.[292,1371,1311,1933]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 8. Stroborineceras felis gen. et sp. nov., holotype MB.C.30454 (Korn et al. 2002 Coll.) from Oued Temertasset. A. Ventral and lateral views. B. Whorl profile. C. Suture line, at ww =15.6 mm, wh=12.7 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902603" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902603/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="79">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
